Unlike anatase and brookite, rutile does not exhibit power law recombination kinetics. Rather, a ‘log-linear’ decay is observed. Empirically, we can describe this behaviour with a log decay (Eq. 2), which produces a high quality fit to the data:2[h+](t)=−Alog(t)+c\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
