In principle, the exponent of the power law decay can be influenced by multiple trapping of electrons or holes. However, the exponential tail of states falling away from the valance band edge measured by Weng lends credence to the hypothesis that the multiple trapping of holes strongly contributes to the observed dynamics27. Quantitatively, this is reflected in differences in the exponent of the power law (α) as kTα\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
