				\begin{document}$$IPCE( \% )=\frac{{J}_{SS}}{{I}_{\lambda }}\cdot 100$$\end{document}where JSS (electrons cm−2 
                        s−2) is the steady state photocurrent density at a given wavelength and Iλ (photons cm−2 
                        s−2) is the flux of the monochromatic light source.
